&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Macmillan Recovery Package Programme Lead&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed term period - 1 Year&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 8a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced manager to lead the continued implementation of the trusts Macmillan recovery package programme, including stratified pathways, across Croydon University Hospital and the Croydon community&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is important to Croydon, and the successful candidate will be expected to engage with all stakeholders to deliver services across all areas of the trust including external users such as primary, community and Royal Marsden Partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A history of managing complex projects and collaborative working are important for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is a fixed term contract for twelve months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information on the role, please contact Sara McGee, General Manager to discuss in more detail&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews: tbc&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sara McGee, General Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: saramcgee@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 020 8401 3000 ext 5331&lt;/p&gt;
